race_titles.description: Gov. Gretchen Whitmer, a first-term Democrat, is being challenged by Tudor Dixon, a conservative media personality with the political backing of the state’s powerful DeVos family.

John Gibbs, a former Trump administration housing official who ousted Representative Peter Meijer in the Republican primary, is facing Hillary Scholten, the Democratic nominee, in a highly competitive race.

Representative Elissa Slotkin, a Democrat, is seeking re-election in this redrawn district. Ms. Slotkin, a former White House national security aide and intelligence briefer, is facing Tom Barrett, a Republican state senator.
Representative Dan Kildee, a vulnerable Democratic incumbent, is being challenged by the Republican Paul Junge, a former TV news anchor and prosecutor who worked in the Trump administration.

Dana Nessel, the state’s attorney general who ran unopposed in the Democratic primary, will face Matthew DePerno, a Republican trial lawyer and conspiracy theorist who has stoked false claims that the 2020 election was stolen.

race_titles.default_title: Proposal 1: Adjust Term Limits and Financial Disclosure Rules for State Officials

race_titles.description: This measure would add several voting- and election-related policies to the state constitution, including the creation of a nine-day early voting period and a requirement that the state fund absentee ballot dropboxes.
race_titles.default_title: Proposal 2: Add Voting Policies to State Constitution

race_titles.description: The proposal would create a state constitutional right to reproductive freedom, including decisions “about all matters relating to pregnancy,” such as abortion and contraception.
race_titles.default_title: Proposal 3: Constitutional Right to Reproductive Freedom

race_titles.description: Jocelyn Benson, the Democratic secretary of state, has confronted repeated harassment from far-right election deniers. She faces a Republican candidate, Kristina Karamo, who has spread falsehoods about that year’s presidential contest.
